  "text": "There is also evidence of increased cholesterol synthesis to compensate for saponin-induced excretion [CITATION_1] . Dietary sarsasaponin failed to lower the cholesterol content of egg yolk or the serum of laying hens even though it increased the excretion of cholesterol and decreased the transfer of dietary cholesterol to the eggs [CITATION_2] .",
